# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  Trivy False Positive Overrides                              ║
# ║  CVE IDs listed here are IGNORED during Trivy scans         ║
# ║  Format: one CVE per line with a required comment explaining ║
# ║  WHY it is a false positive or accepted risk                 ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

# EXAMPLE — remove this line and replace with real entries:
# CVE-2023-XXXXX  # False positive: affects feature X which is not used in this codebase

# HOW TO ADD AN EXCEPTION:
# 1. Run: trivy image <image> --format json to get CVE IDs
# 2. Research the CVE to confirm it's a false positive or accepted risk
# 3. Add the CVE ID here with a comment explaining:
#    - Why it's a false positive OR
#    - Why it's an accepted risk (e.g., "not exploitable in our deployment config")
#    - Date of review and reviewer name
# 4. Schedule a review date no more than 90 days out
# 5. Open a PR with the exception — it will be reviewed by the security team
